{
  "article_id": "TheGalvestonDailyNews1933",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "In compliment to the charming"
      },
      {
        "text": "Miss Nell Skaggs",
        "entity_key": "nska",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who will depart on Wednesday after enjoying the fall season here,"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Bryan F. Williams",
        "entity_key": "bwil",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "will entertain this afternoon with a bridge tea at her home. Guests at the event will include members of the younger social set."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Malcom Walker",
        "entity_key": "mwal",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of"
      },
      {
        "text": "Chicago",
        "entity_key": "ci_chic",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "has arrived here to spend the winter and will reside at the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Highland Inn",
        "entity_key": "highlandinn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Walker",
        "entity_key": "mwal",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "has visited here previously."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Members of [the]"
      },
      {
        "text": "George Washington Chapter",
        "entity_key": "dar_gwa",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ","
      },
      {
        "text": "Daughters of the American Revolution",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", were entertained Thursday afternoon at the home of"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. C. A. Vedder",
        "entity_key": "cve",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Two interesting papers were read, one, \"Morris Jumel House\" given by"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. C. G. Waller",
        "entity_key": "cwa",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", being part of the program for the year on historic buildings of America."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The other paper, read by"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. L. C. Van Name",
        "entity_key": "lva",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was entitled \"The Lone Woman of San Nicholas Island,\" and dealt with the story of a woman,"
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who lived for 40 years alone on the"
      },
      {
        "text": "island of San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", off the"
      },
      {
        "text": "coast of California",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", building her own shelter and making her own garments from the materials found there. She was accidentally abandoned when"
      },
      {
        "text": "missionaries",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "removed"
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "from"
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Van Name",
        "entity_key": "lva",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "explained that the"
      },
      {
        "text": "D. A. R. chapter of Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "dar_sb",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "had erected a tablet in memory of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Miss Sue Larson",
        "entity_key": "sla",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "conducted a general discussion on national activities of the"
      },
      {
        "text": "D. A. R.",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mrs[.] Vedder",
        "entity_key": "cve",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was assisted in entertaining by"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Cortes Pauls",
        "entity_key": "cpau",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The"
      },
      {
        "text": "Phi Alpha Sigma Fraternity",
        "entity_key": "frat_pas",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "will entertain with an informal holiday gathering atthe fraternity house Wednesday evening."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Bernard Bernadoni",
        "entity_key": "bbe",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", president of the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Galveston Reserve Officers",
        "entity_key": "mi_gro",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and first lieutenant of infantry reserves, will be among those going from here to attend the military reception and dance to be given tonight at"
      },
      {
        "text": "River Oaks",
        "entity_key": "riveroaks",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "by the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Houston reserve officers",
        "entity_key": "mi_hro",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ]
  ]
}